Commentators generally agree that the appointment of John Bolton as National Security Advisor by President Trump is a positive choice. They believe that Bolton's experience and expertise will help confront the challenges of a dangerous world and continue the accomplishments of outgoing NSA H.R. McMaster. Many commentators highlight Bolton's ability to prepare the President for the upcoming meeting with Kim Jong Un and his no-nonsense approach to dealing with international threats. They also emphasize his conservative foreign-policy thought and support for U.N. reform. Overall, commentators believe that Bolton will be a strong addition to the White House team and will prioritize America's interests in the global arena.